timelineItems.title: GOAL: Sebastian Lletget scores, capping of terrific passing sequence

timelineItems.desc: The LA Galaxy rolls into Columbus as both teams are looking for a crucial win.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: Columbus Crew SC vs. Los Angeles Galaxy | June 13, 2015

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Full time: #CrewSC 1, #LAGalaxy 1. Crew extend their winless streak to six games while the Galaxy take a hard-earned point on the road.

timelineItems.name: TWC SportsNet
timelineItems.text: FT: The #LAGalaxy play to a draw on the road in Cleveland, 1-1. #CLBvLA http://t.co/20uSzIGy3K

timelineItems.desc: The LA Galaxy rolls into Columbus as both teams are looking for a crucial win.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Columbus Crew SC vs. Los Angeles Galaxy | June 13, 2015

timelineItems.name: The Pit: S&E
timelineItems.text: 35' - Cross into the box finds Kamara, but he can't head it down. Attempt goes over the bar for a goal kick. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 35': #CrewSC moving the ball around well. Finlay hits a lofted cross from the right wing and Kamara gets a header attempt. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Corner Of The Galaxy
timelineItems.text: Husidic can’t do that. He needs to shoot that. We had the ball in the box. STOP PASSING IT. #LAGalaxy

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 35’ Kamara got a header off a long ball, but it goes over. #CrewSC offense not really effective so far.

timelineItems.name: that guy
timelineItems.text: Yeah. I like this Lletget guy. #lagalaxy

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: WATCH: Sebastian Lletget takes Robbie Rogers' layoff and finishes in style --> http://t.co/qwL16JRSou #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Seeing them in person, I'm struck by how physically imposing this #LAGalaxy team is. And not just Leonardo/Gonzalez.

timelineItems.name: Levi Combs
timelineItems.text: Not really sure what Kamara is doing tonight... #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC lucky they didn't get burned worse there. #LAGalaxy still up 1-0 44'

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Rogers needed to get that shot off several steps sooner #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Blistering shot, but it's straight at Penedo from an angle it's very hard to score from. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Lake County Legion
timelineItems.text: I honestly want to see Parkhurst taken out for Wahl come 2nd half! Parkhurst has not impressed me all season... #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Corner Of The Galaxy
timelineItems.text: Edson Buddle was supposed to start… but because he didn’t, the @LAGalaxy are winning and look young and quick. Thanks Buddle. #LAGalaxy

timelineItems.name: Adam Serrano
timelineItems.text: HT - #LAGalaxy looking dangerous on the attack and very compact on the defense. One of the best halves they've played this season. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Andrew Schmidt
timelineItems.text: LA are moving much better and showing much better. Still need to finish some of these to walk out of here with 3 points, I think. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: I've heard people say this #CrewSC team wouldn't be drastically better if Wil Trapp was playing. I posit that it absolutely would be.

timelineItems.name: Nino Torres
timelineItems.text: Forget about the possession. One of the major reasons #LAGalaxy is dominating this game : 67.5% of Duels won. #CrewSC #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: The Calzone
timelineItems.text: As much as I want to rage about goals the #CrewSC defense is a shambles. It starts with Parkhurst.

timelineItems.name: LA Galaxy
timelineItems.text: Aaaaaaaaaand we’re back for the second half in Cowtown. Watch live on @TWCSportsNet: http://t.co/qQjHyfBhwc #CLBvLA http://t.co/ukdQcuBWyi

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Pro tip: when passing, make sure a player on your team is in the vicinity of the receiving end of the pass. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: The Pit: S&E
timelineItems.text: Thankfully, the second wave of storms that looked inbound for Columbus is trending north. Looks like we'll finish tonight. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 48': Higuaín with a great through ball to Finlay, who plays it inside to Meram. Defended well by LA. #CrewSC #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: One of the best chances #CrewSC has seen all night involves a Finlay cross to Kamara...with 4 LA defenders in the area. Corner the result.

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC have really upped their tempo so far in this second half. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Columbus Wired
timelineItems.text: The second half is now underway #clbvla http://t.co/8kGqIk4Xn8

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Much better from #CrewSC in the 2nd half. Crisper passing, finding more space in the middle, using the wings.

timelineItems.name: The Pit: S&E
timelineItems.text: 52' - Chance for #CrewSC as the Black and Gold go on the attack. However, it looked like all of L.A. was in the penalty area for the cross.

timelineItems.name: Adam Serrano
timelineItems.text: 51' #CrewSC putting numbers forward but the #LAGalaxy defense has remained compact and organized. Gonzalez doing very well vs. Kamara.

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: That sequence in the 52nd minute may have been the best chance of the game for #CrewSC. Two decent crosses, Galaxy defense unable to clear

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: That shot by Kamara was the first SOG for #CrewSC all game. Did not have one in the first half. #LAGalaxy

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 55': Through the first 10 minutes of play this half, the ball has barely left #CrewSC's attacking third. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: For flying around the world this week - Meram is looking pretty sharp so far #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 58' Higuain dribbles forward, cuts inside and lays the ball off to...no one. He angrily gestures to the space to his #CrewSC teammates.

timelineItems.name: Corner Of The Galaxy
timelineItems.text: Good sequence from @LAGalaxy. Husidic did well to keep the ball. Good passing. Two good chances on goal. #LAGalaxy

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Official attendance- 21,051. First #CrewSC sellout of the year at expanded capacity.

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Columbus Crew SC 1, LA Galaxy 1. Federico Higuain (Columbus Crew SC) right footed shot from the center of the box to the bottom left corner
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Federico Higuain's great finish equalizes for Columbus

timelineItems.name: Adam Serrano
timelineItems.text: 64' Another solid play from Gonzalez who slides in the stride of Meram and forces the Crew SC striker to fire it wide. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 66’ Finlay again behind the defense. His deep cutback cross finds Higuain. Cool to tie it. 1-1 #CrewSC.

timelineItems.name: Josh Mlot
timelineItems.text: Great pass by Tchani made that goal. Worth noting Pipa had won back possession for #CrewSC about a minute earlier.

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Bruce Arena's blind spot for Leonardo still fascinates me. #CLBvLA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Andrew Schmidt
timelineItems.text: One goal was never going to be enough. LA squandered chances when they were generating them. Now working against the run of play. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Andrew Reynolds
timelineItems.text: Higuain with the goal #CrewSC #whatwelivefor http://t.co/hyOVlPPezD

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Kei Kamara (Columbus Crew SC) right footed shot from the centre of the box misses to the right.
timelineItems.title: SKILL: Justin Meram pulls off inadvertent backheel flick

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Roles seem reversed in this half. Could we see Francis go on a swashbuckling run like Rogers did? #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Mitch Meadows
timelineItems.text: Close to action with Steve Clark #CrewSC @ColumbusCrewSC http://t.co/xAZ0Fdb8Au

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Federico Higuain now with 31 career goals, two behind Guillermo Barros Schelotto in sixth place in #CrewSC history.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Schmidt
timelineItems.text: I can’t get on board with the “best 45 minutes of LA’s season” meme. Best first 15, maybe. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Seriously, Pogatetz has been brilliant yet again. Make sure the communcation problems never happen again. #CrewSC need him

timelineItems.name: The Pit: S&E
timelineItems.text: Pipa's through balls in the second half have been a thing of beauty. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Patrick Guldan
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC pushing for the winner and #LAGalaxy would love to hit them on the break.

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Justin Meram (Columbus Crew SC) header from the center of the box is saved in the top center of the goal.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Jaime Penedo pulls off big save on Meram

timelineItems.name: Sean Cahill
timelineItems.text: Pogatetz has been an absolute rock tonight. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: On. Point. Great header from Meram, fantastic save from Penedo. Robbed. #CrewSC #LAGalaxy

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC has to hope Schoenfeld can run at the defense for seven or eight minutes like Finlay did for 84.

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: I like the move by Berhalter in a tie game like this to bring on a 2nd forward late; definitely not trying to settle for a point. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Andrew Schmidt
timelineItems.text: No complaints about Lletget’s showing tonight. Better effort & better results than anybody else wearing white. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 89' Pogatetz, again, with a saving clearance. Has happened a lot tonight for #CrewSC.

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Jiménez seems to have taken a knock. Took him a while to get up but moving around now. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: The Pit: S&E
timelineItems.text: Higuain has gone down at the top of the penalty arc. We didn't see what happened but play has been stopped. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Sean Maslin
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC's crosses into the box have been promising. But credit to the #LAGalaxy defense. Really putting in a shift. #CLBvLA

timelineItems.name: Setting the Table
timelineItems.text: Enough with the Schoenfeld experiment. Totally ineffective. Go with Gall or Speas and take your chances. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Aaron G. Butts
timelineItems.text: Looking like the match might end in a tie despite a good second half for #CrewSC
